All such services are independent and subject to their own terms of service,
acceptable use policies, and requirements.

Users who modify, fork, self-host, or otherwise deploy the Software are solely
responsible for ensuring that their use complies with all applicable third-party
terms.

Forked or modified versions of the Software must not represent themselves as
the original Software when interacting with third-party services. This includes,
where applicable:
- Using a distinct User-Agent identifier
- Providing accurate contact information
- Clearly distinguishing forked versions from the original Software

Failure to comply with third-party service requirements or misuse of such services
in connection with the Software constitutes a violation of this license and
results in automatic termination of rights granted herein.

